</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ubelhaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Belhaven</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 8/15/02 4:39:16 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ufueganlegionkiller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fuegan Legionkiller</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(8/15/02 5:28:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=465.topic&index=295>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> Nice thread...you folks should put your heads together and solve world hunger, it would probably be easier then this mess. <br>
<br>
Seems to me that the list, though time consuming offers some sense of a guarantee to a cleric that regardless of guild size he/she will get the drop assuming they have the patience to wait it out.<br>
<br>
 Its really a simple debate. Do you want to go FFA in which case &quot;power&quot; guilds can decide that all of their twinks need Epics and completely shut out everyone else. Or they can make matters worse by coming to an agreement amongst themselves in which case you'll really be at their mercy. One of the arguments made is that no one wants to wait the months and months required by the list. Seems that its a better alternative then &quot;maybe never&quot;.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately you're playing a game where 9 out of 10 times might makes right.<br>
<br>
Seems impossible to limit Clerics by what stage of their epic they're on or if its a twink since a lot of people play their secondary characters as much as their first. But you can do damage control. You don't like having a list that's 12 months long then limit the people that can be on it at any one time. Say something like 10 Clerics so there's at least a light at the end of the tunnel for those having to wait. Make it the responsibility of the next cleric to contact the list holder in person when the 10th spot is freed up. It puts the responsibility on the aspiring next Cleric to keep up with the situation and its in their best interest to hang out and help so they can be the first there for that now open 10th spot.<br>
<br>
Limit the number of clerics from any one guild that can be on that list. Be reasonable but make the larger guilds put a little more effort into whom they're going to send after their Epic next. Might cut back on twinks and secondary a little.<br>
<br>
Email the mods of this board and see if they can post a list, restrict the access to it and see if they'll be kind enough to update. Its not like it would be a daily chore. And it would give the Quellious community a running record of who and when.<br>
<br>
Regardless of how this is all decided it should be done so by the Clerics of the server and agreed upon by the majority. If its not then nothing, no matter how well in design will ever work.<br>
<br>
Fue <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ufueganlegionkiller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fuegan Legionkiller</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 8/15/02 6:14:59 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uledronesoultaker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ledrone Soultaker</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Dar Knight</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(8/16/02 6:59:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=465.topic&index=296>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> &quot;Limit the number of clerics from any one guild that can be on that list. Be reasonable but make the larger guilds put a little more effort into whom they're going to send after their Epic next. Might cut back on twinks and secondary a little.&quot;<br>
